  "description": [
    "BACON OFFERS BILL 10 CURB CHILD LABOR International New Service A bill drafted by noted lawyers designed to effectively halt child labor and ease the fight being Waged throughout the country over the child labor amendment was to be thrust before the House today by Representative Bacon R of New Work The measure following the Supreme Court decision in the convict labor case forbids trans portation of goods made by child labor into States prohibiting sale of this class of goods The bill it was explained could be written into law even if the child labor amendment is not ratified Bacon declared The object of those opposing child labor is to drive out sweat hop labor of children and in general to keep them out of in dustrial occupations until they re 18 years old with some ex ceptions My bill which was drafted by noted constitutional authorities offers away to accomplish this purpose New York State for example has a strong antichild labor law which generally has proven satisfactory It could prevent States permitting child labor from sending the products of child labor to its millions of buyers The measure would relieve the fears of those who believe that"
  ],
